  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.8.17-stable-8bbe7207\r\nOS & Version: Windows 10 64-Bit\r\nCPU: i9-7980XE\r\nMemory: 128GB DDR4 SDRAM\r\nStorage: Intel DC P4600 4TB PCIe NVMe SSD\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nGeth is able to sync a full / archive node on a Windows 10 64-Bit machine under a Standard User account (non-admin), with a 4TB NVMe SSD & Gigabit internet connection. Admin privileges were enabled for geth.exe.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nGeth crashes multiple times after several days of syncing. Attempt 1 crashed around ETH mainnet block 5118645. Attempt 2 crashed atround ETH mainnet block 3996915.\r\n\r\nEnabling --verbosity 5 reveals the following exception:\r\n\r\nException 0xc0000005 0x8 0xc0000a17c8 0xc0000a17c8\r\nPC=0xc0000a17c8\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/13838584/48245562-6eabae00-e3b9-11e8-9b7c-d49cce7c3014.png)\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\ngeth --syncmode=full --gcmode=archive --cache=43581 --maxpeers=25000 --datadir=\"B:\\Chains\\Ethereum\\Geth\\Mainnet\"",
